{{For|an estate on [[Repulse Bay]] in [[Hong Kong]]|Larvotto (Hong Kong)}} {{Infobox settlement |name = Larvotto |settlement_type = Ward of Monaco |official_name = |other_name = |native_name = |nickname = |motto = |image_skyline = Monaco landscape.JPG |imagesize = 310px |image_caption = Coastline |image_flag = |flag_size = |image_seal = |seal_size = |image_shield = |shield_size = |image_blank_emblem = |blank_emblem_size = |image_map = Larvotto in Monaco.svg |mapsize = 310px |map_caption = Location in Monaco |image_map1 = |mapsize1 = |map_caption1 = |pushpin_map = France |pushpin_label_position = left |pushpin_map_caption=Location in relation to France |pushpin_mapsize=300 |subdivision_type = [[Countries of the world|Country]] |subdivision_name = {{flag|Monaco}} |subdivision_type1 = |subdivision_name1 = |subdivision_type2 = |subdivision_name2 = |seat_type = |seat = |government_type = |leader_title = |leader_name = |leader_title1 = <!-- for places with, say, both a mayor and a city manager --> |leader_name1 = |established_title = |established_date = |area_magnitude = |area_land_km2 = |area_water_km2 = |area_total_km2 = 0.217932 |area_land_sq_mi = |area_water_sq_mi = |area_water_percent = |area_urban_km2 = |area_urban_sq_mi = |area_metro_km2 = |area_metro_sq_mi = |population_as_of = 2008 |population_footnotes = |population_note = |population_total = 5091 |population_density_km2 = 23360 |population_density_sq_mi = |population_metro = |population_density_metro_km2 = |population_density_metro_sq_mi = |population_urban = |population_density_urban_km2 = |population_density_urban_mi2 = |timezone = |utc_offset = |coordinates = {{coord|43|44|48|N|7|26|00|E|region:MC|display=inline,title}} |elevation_footnotes = |elevation_m = |elevation_ft = |postal_code_type = <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... --> |postal_code = |area_code = |website = |footnotes = }}
'''Larvotto''' is the easternmost [[Administrative divisions of Monaco|Ward]] in the [[Monaco|Principality of Monaco]]. Larvotto was incorporated in [[Monte Carlo]].<ref name=autogenerated4>{{Cite web |url=http://en.gouv.mc/Policy-Practice/The-Economy/Analysis-and-Statistics/Publications/Population-census |title=Census |access-date=2013-05-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140604103941/http://en.gouv.mc/Policy-Practice/The-Economy/Analysis-and-Statistics/Publications/Population-census |archive-date=2014-06-04 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref>
==Landmarks== [[File:Promenade du Larvotto - panoramio (1).jpg|thumb|135px|left|Larvotto Promenade]] Larvotto is northeast of [[Monte Carlo]] and [[La Rousse]]. It borders [[Roquebrune-Cap-Martin]], [[Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur]], [[France]], to the northeast.
The [[Grimaldi Forum]], a conference and congress centre, is located on the seafront of Larvotto.
[[Avenue Princesse Grace]], located alongside ''Larvotto Beach'', was the world's most expensive street to live on.<ref name=autogenerated1>{{Cite web |url=http://www.overseaspropertymall.com/luxury-property/the-10-most-expensive-streets-in-the-world-2011-update/ |title=The 10 Most Expensive Streets in the World [2011 Update&#93; - Overseas Property Blog :: guide to international real estate investment<!-- Bot generated title --> |access-date=2011-10-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111020165126/http://www.overseaspropertymall.com/luxury-property/the-10-most-expensive-streets-in-the-world-2011-update/ |archive-date=2011-10-20 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref> The average apartment was {{convert|6970|$/sqft|$/m2}}.<ref name=autogenerated1 /><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://blogs.wsj.com/wealth/2008/08/05/the-10-most-expensive-streets-in-the-world/ |title=The 10 Most Expensive Streets in the World - The Wealth Report - WSJ<!-- Bot generated title --> |access-date=2017-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161016121616/http://blogs.wsj.com/wealth/2008/08/05/the-10-most-expensive-streets-in-the-world/ |archive-date=2016-10-16 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url= https://www.theguardian.com/money/2009/jul/22/worlds-most-expensive-streets |title= Credit crunch reaches world's most expensive streets {{!}} Money {{!}} guardian.co.uk |access-date=2016-12-15 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170329034504/https://www.theguardian.com/money/2009/jul/22/worlds-most-expensive-streets |archive-date=2017-03-29 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url= http://www.nicematin.com/article/monaco/princesse-grace-%C2%AB-rue-la-plus-chere-du-monde-%C2%BB.234118.html |title=Princesse-Grace, « rue la plus chère du monde » {{!}} Nice-Matin |access-date= 2012-08-19 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20121122144224/http://www.nicematin.com/article/monaco/princesse-grace-%C2%AB-rue-la-plus-chere-du-monde-%C2%BB.234118.html |archive-date= 2012-11-22 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url= http://www.montecarlo-realestate.com/en/quartiers/ |title=Real Estate Monaco Monte-Carlo<!-- Bot generated title --> |access-date=2011-10-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111101193429/http://www.montecarlo-realestate.com/en/quartiers |archive-date=2011-11-01 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref> The [[Japanese Garden, Monaco|Japanese Garden]] is a municipal park on the Avenue Princesse Grace.
