{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}
'''Sir Ronald Urwick Cooke''', [[Fellow of the Royal Geographical Society|FRGS]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] (born 1 September 1941<ref name=Debretts>[http://www.debretts.com/people/biographies/browse/c/6838/Ronald%20Urwick%20(Ron)%20COOKE.aspx Debrett's People of Today] Sir Ron Cooke</ref>) is a Professor of [[geography]] and [[geomorphology]] who was [[Vice-Chancellor]] of the [[University of York]] from 1993 to 2002.<ref name="york2001">[http://www.york.ac.uk/admin/presspr/pressreleases/vcretires.htm Professor Ron Cooke to retire as Vice-Chancellor in 2002], University of York Press Release, 1 May 2001</ref>

==Life==
Cooke's academic career began as a lecturer in the Department of Geography at [[University College London]] in 1961: he rose to the position of Professor in 1981 and Vice-Provost (1991&ndash;3) at the same institution.<ref name=Debretts/><ref name="york2001"/>   From 1993 to 2002 he was Vice-Chancellor of the University of York.<ref name="york2001"/> Cooke was appointed chair of the [[Joint Information Systems Committee]] (JISC) in 2004.<ref name="JISC">[http://www.jisc.ac.uk/home/events/2008/04/jiscconference08/roncooke.aspx Sir Ron Cooke, JISC Chair], JISC, accessed 26 January 2010</ref>  He was a Trustee of the [[National Museum of Science and Industry]] from 2005 to 2008.<ref>[http://www.york.ac.uk/admin/presspr/pressreleases/vcscimuseum.htm Sir Ron Cooke to be trustee of the National Museum of Science and Industry], University of York Press Release, 6 June 2002</ref>

He lives in [[York]] where he is active in city life, for instance in fund-raising for the restoration of [[York Minster]], and in planning and restoration through the York Civic Trust.<ref>[http://www.yorkminster.org/news/story193/substantial-donation-from-york-civic-trust.html Substantial donation from York Civic Trust], York Minster Development Office News, 8 November 2007</ref> The York Civic Trust also published his monograph ''Why York is Special''.<ref>[http://www.yorkcivictrust.co.uk/?idno=759 Why York Is Special], [[York Civic Trust]], York, accessed 14 January 2015</ref>

==Honours==
He was awarded the [[Gold Medal (RGS)|Founder's Medal]] of the [[Royal Geographical Society]] (RGS) in 1994,<ref>[http://www.rgs.org/NR/rdonlyres/C5962519-882A-4C67-803D-0037308C756D/0/GoldMedalrecipents.pdf Gold Medal recipients], Royal Geographical Society, accessed 26 January 2010</ref> and was President of the RGS  from 2000 to 2003.<ref name="york2006">[http://www.york.gov.uk/news/newsarchive/2006/march/161208 Professor Sir Ronald Cooke - Honorary Freeman], York City Council, 7 March 2006</ref> In 2002, he received the [[Scottish Geographical Medal]] of the [[Royal Scottish Geographical Society]].<ref>[http://www.rsgs.org/awardsandmedals/sgm.html Scottish Geography Medal], Royal Scottish Geographical Society, accessed 26 January 2010</ref> He was [[Knight Bachelor|knighted]] for services to higher education in the Queen's 2002 New Year's Honours list.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/education/2001/dec/31/highereducation.uk New Year honours in higher education], Donald MacLeod, guardian.co.uk, Monday 31 December 2001</ref> In 2006, he was made Honorary Freeman of the City of York.<ref name="york2006"/>

The Ron Cooke Hub at the Heslington East campus of the [[University of York]] was named in his honour.

